| Priority | Change | Why |
|---|---|---|
| High | Add error-handling middleware that never leaks `err.stack` | Prevents info disclosure |
| High | Add `helmet()` | Baseline security headers |
| High | Validate all `req.query` / `req.params` / `req.body` with a schema lib | Prevents injection & malformed input crashes |
| High | Add `express.json({ limit: '100kb' })` before any JSON route | Prevents DoS via huge payloads |
| Medium | Add `express-rate-limit` | Mitigates brute force / scraping |
| Medium | Configure CORS explicitly | Avoid unintended cross-origin exposure |
| Medium | Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT | Avoids dropped connections on deploy |
| Low | Replace `console.log` with structured logger | Better observability |
| Low | Consider omitting PII (email) from public `/users` | Minimize data exposure |

