app.get('/internal/health', requireAuth, (_req, res) => {
  res.json({ status: 'ok', uptime: process.uptime(), timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });
});
```

### 6. Hard-coded port and no TLS termination guidance (A05)
`app.listen(3000, ...)` ignores environment config and assumes plaintext. In production, bind via env and always front with HTTPS (reverse proxy or native TLS). Also trust the proxy so `req.ip` and `X-Forwarded-*` are correct for rate limiting and logging.

```js
