app.set('trust proxy', 1); // behind a single reverse proxy
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
```

### 7. No error handler — unhandled errors can leak stack traces (A05 / A09)
Add a terminal error handler that logs server-side and returns a generic message:

```js
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  // structured log; do NOT send err.stack to the client
  console.error({ msg: 'unhandled', path: req.path, err: err.message });
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'internal_error' });
});

